Order of execution for a junior engineer
Task 1 (install + provider) — no behaviour change, just wires up the library
Task 2 (query keys) — no behaviour change, just a constants file
Task 3 (query hooks) — no behaviour change, hooks exist but nothing uses them yet
Task 4 (UserContext) — migrate the one context, verify login + preferences still work
Task 5.1 (Patterns page) — simplest page, good first migration to verify the pattern
Task 5.2 (Dashboard) — second migration
Task 5.3 (Cashflow) — most complex, do last among the pages
Task 5.4, 5.5 (remaining pages)
Task 6 (remove manual wiring)
Task 7 (error boundaries)
Task 8 (cleanup)
Test each page after each step. The migration is safe to do incrementally — old pages and new pages can coexist during migration.